📘 Pralay.VulX – Command Line User Manual
Version: 2.0
Author: Vimal Bijalwan

This manual covers all command-line options, usage examples, output interpretation, and troubleshooting tips for Pralay.VulX – the advanced vulnerability scanner.

1. Synopsis
bash
python3 pralay_vulx.py <target> [options]
2. Description
Pralay.VulX performs:

Network port scanning with service version detection (via Nmap)

CVE matching using the vulners script and NVD API

Web crawling to find all links and forms

Parameter fuzzing with 7 vulnerability classes (SQLi, XSS, LFI, RCE, SSTI, XXE, SSRF)

Live progress indicator (percentage, current parameter, payload type)

Firewall evasion (stealth and Tor modes)

Detailed text report generation

3. Options
Option	Type	Description	Default
target	positional	IP address or hostname (e.g., 192.168.1.1 or example.com)	Required
--ports	string	Port range to scan (e.g., 80,443, 1-1000, 22,8080-8085)	1-1000
--crawl-url	URL	Base URL for crawling + fuzzing (e.g., http://target.com)	None (no web fuzzing)
--stealth	flag	Enable firewall evasion: slow scan (-T1), decoy IPs, fragmentation, source port 53	Disabled
--tor	flag	Route all traffic through Tor (requires tor service running)	Disabled
--no-nmap	flag	Skip Nmap scan – only perform web crawling/fuzzing	Disabled
-h, --help	flag	Show help message and exit	-
4. How It Works (Step by Step)
If Nmap is not skipped:

Runs nmap -sV --script vulners -p <ports> <target>

With --stealth, adds evasion flags

With --tor, prefixes proxychains4 -q

Output is parsed for CVE IDs and CVSS scores

If --crawl-url is provided:

Crawls the given URL (depth 1) to discover all links and forms

Extracts all parameter names from <input>, <textarea>, <select>

If no parameters found, falls back to a built-in wordlist of common params

Fuzzing phase:

Each parameter is tested with all payloads from 7 categories (SQLi, XSS, LFI, RCE, SSTI, XXE, SSRF)

Live progress: percentage, current parameter index, current payload type

Detected vulnerabilities are stored with the exact URL and payload

Report generation:

Combines CVE findings and web vulnerability findings

Saves to PralayVulX_report_<target>.txt

Prints summary to console

5. Usage Examples
5.1 Basic Nmap scan (no web fuzzing)
bash
python3 pralay_vulx.py 192.168.1.1 --ports 22,80,443
5.2 Web fuzzing only (fastest)
bash
python3 pralay_vulx.py example.com --no-nmap --crawl-url http://example.com
5.3 Full test (network + web)
bash
python3 pralay_vulx.py example.com --ports 1-1000 --crawl-url http://example.com
5.4 Stealth mode (avoid simple firewalls)
bash
python3 pralay_vulx.py target.com --ports 80,443 --crawl-url http://target.com --stealth
5.5 Tor + stealth (maximum anonymity)
bash
sudo systemctl start tor
python3 pralay_vulx.py darkweb.onion --ports 80 --crawl-url http://darkweb.onion --stealth --tor
5.6 Scan specific ports + fuzz
bash
python3 pralay_vulx.py 10.0.0.5 --ports 8080,8443 --crawl-url http://10.0.0.5:8080
5.7 Test local Juice Shop (legal playground)
bash
python3 pralay_vulx.py juice-shop.herokuapp.com --no-nmap --crawl-url http://juice-shop.herokuapp.com
