7. Firewall Evasion Details
When --stealth is used, the underlying Nmap command becomes:

bash
nmap -sV --script vulners -p <ports> <target> \
  -T1 -f --data-length 200 -D RND:10 --source-port 53 --max-retries 1 --host-timeout 30s
-T1 : Very slow (paranoid) timing – less likely to trigger IDS

-f : Fragment packets (bypass basic filters)

--data-length 200 : Append random data (evade signature detection)

-D RND:10 : Use 10 random decoy IPs (your real IP is hidden among them)

--source-port 53 : Pretend traffic comes from DNS port (many firewalls allow DNS)

--max-retries 1 : Retry only once (reduces noise)

--host-timeout 30s : Skip unresponsive hosts after 30 seconds

Performance note: Stealth scans are much slower (can take 10-30 minutes for 1000 ports). Use it only when necessary.

8. Tor Mode Setup
To use --tor:

Install Tor: sudo apt install tor (Kali/Ubuntu)

Start the service: sudo systemctl start tor

Verify it’s running: sudo systemctl status tor

Run Pralay.VulX with --tor

The tool will prefix all Nmap commands with proxychains4 -q. Make sure /etc/proxychains4.conf contains socks4 127.0.0.1 9050 (default). Tor mode also works for crawling and fuzzing.

9. Troubleshooting
Error: nmap: command not found
Install Nmap: sudo apt install nmap -y

Error: ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'bs4'
Install BeautifulSoup: pip install beautifulsoup4

Error: [Errno 2] No such file or directory when running script
Make sure you are in the directory where pralay_vulx.py exists, or use full path.

Scan seems stuck at "Running: nmap ..."
Without stealth: wait up to 3 minutes for 1000 ports.

With stealth: can take 10+ minutes. Be patient.

To stop: Ctrl+C and try with --no-nmap or fewer ports.

No parameters found during crawling
Some sites require login or block crawlers. Use --crawl-url with a deeper depth? (Modify script to increase depth if needed). Alternatively, the tool falls back to a common wordlist.

False positives
Web fuzzing uses simple heuristics. Always manually verify findings before reporting.

10. Reporting & Saving Results
Reports are automatically saved as:

text
PralayVulX_report_<target>.txt
Where <target> is the hostname/IP you scanned (slashes replaced by underscores).

You can also redirect console output:

bash
python3 pralay_vulx.py example.com --no-nmap --crawl-url http://example.com 2>&1 | tee scan.log
11. Uninstall / Clean Up
To remove Pralay.VulX:

bash
rm -rf /path/to/Pralay-VulX
No system-wide files are installed.

